Actor, Blossom Chukwujekw’s ex-wife, Maureen Esisi aka Redvigor has made an announcement directed especially at suitors and those who desire to be her friends. The brand influencer, who was recently in Dubai vacationing with her ‘bae’ Dobi Okonkwo, informed those interested in friendship to prioritise keeping her if they get lucky enough to find her. Sharing a sensual photo, Mama Red wrote: “If you find me, Make it a Priority to KEEP ME. E get Why!” In another post, giving reason why any partner must prioritise keeping her, Esisi said it’s because she’s not easily accessible.   Male organ stops growing at 21 – Aproko doctor     FG lauds blood sisters, Nigeria’s first original…     Femi Adebayo excited as ‘King of thieves’…   She added: “I’m 95% INACCESSIBLE…. ask those who have my Access Card and they will Tell You.” Blossom Chukwujekwu and Maureen Esisi dated for a few months then he propsed to her on her birthday, September 11, 2015. Then, they got hitched in a low-key traditional marriage on December 19, 2015. A glamorous white wedding followed the next year on August 11, a ceremony that was attended by top Nigerian celebrities. However, the marriage packed up in 2019 after the actor called his father-in-law and informed him that he was no longer interested in the union.